<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-03-07</DATELINE><TITLE>The ongoing crises in China illustrate that the assessment of epidemics in isolation is no longer sufficient</TITLE><BODY>Summary The interplay of simultaneous COVID-19, African swine fever, and avian influenza emergencies on global health and industries is constantly evolving and difficult to predict, and therefore warrants further scrutiny. The need for a health network of global scope for the rapid and open exchange of information needs to be strengthened in order to address ongoing and future epidemics under competing resources.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>